      "id": "assistant-1774976956900-ward7s",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Done — I turned both characters into clean reference-sheet prompts optimized for downstream consistency.\n\nWhat’s locked in:\n- **Panda**: adult female panda, natural appearance, no clothing/accessories, soft vulnerable read, clear full-body silhouette\n- **Psychologist**: adult male therapist, muted understated wardrobe, calm thoughtful read, clean professional silhouette\n\nThese are written as reusable reference assets rather than stylized hero images, which is the right move for later video consistency.\n\nNext step: generate the two character-sheet images and review them. What we’re looking for:\n- the panda feels emotionally readable without becoming cartoony\n- the psychologist feels warm and credible, not generic stock-photo corporate\n- both have stable, uncluttered silhouettes that will hold up across shots\n\nOnce those images are in, we can either tighten them or move straight into storyboard review before locking keyframes."
