      "id": "assistant-1774982875294-eywm9f",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Done — all 10 keyframe sidecar prompts are now prepared for the planned shots.\n\nWhat I locked in:\n- every keyframe follows the approved storyboard shot\n- each prompt is tuned for still-image generation, not motion\n- character consistency is anchored to the approved panda and psychologist sheets\n- the emotional shifts are subtle and continuous rather than over-acted\n- the storyboard board is referenced as the upstream composition guide for each shot\n\nThe shape is strong:\n- **SHOT-01** holds the room and relationship\n- **SHOT-02** lets the panda’s confession land sincerely\n- **SHOT-03** gives the psychologist calm, non-performative authority\n- **SHOT-04** captures the internal crack and honest admission\n- **SHOT-05** resolves into shared warmth without getting sentimental\n\nNext step: generate the keyframe stills and review them before moving into motion planning.\n\nWhen you review, look for:\n- **character continuity**: panda markings, psychologist face, proportions, wardrobe consistency\n- **shot continuity**: clean progression from wide to tighter coverage and back to shared frame\n- **performance accuracy**: vulnerable and restrained, never cartoony or sitcom-broad\n- **environment consistency**: same office language across all shots\n- **anchor contrast**: start/end frames should feel related but meaningfully different where needed\n\nOnce the stills are back, I can do a fast creative review and then turn the sequence into the shot plan and video prompts."
    },
